---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="DonjonSec Privacy Policy. Learn what data the Donjon Platform collects, what it does not collect, and how your data is used."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy-950 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-400">
          Last updated: February 2026
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy Content -->
  <section class="bg-navy-900 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="space-y-12">

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            This Privacy Policy describes how DonjonSec ("we," "us," "our") collects, uses, and handles information in connection with the Donjon Platform software ("Software"). This policy applies to all editions of the Software: Community, Pro, Enterprise, and MSSP.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- What We Collect -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">What We Collect</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            The Software may collect and transmit the following data to DonjonSec servers for the purposes described in this policy:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">License Activation Data</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- License key status, activation timestamps, and edition tier information used for license validation and compliance.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Version Information</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Software version, build number, and update status to ensure you are running the latest version and to deliver relevant updates.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Usage Statistics</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Aggregate, anonymized statistics on which features and scanners are used and how frequently. No specific scan data is included.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Error Reports</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Crash reports, error codes, and stack traces to help us diagnose and fix bugs. These reports do not contain personal data or assessment content.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">System Configuration</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Operating system type and version, available memory, processor type, and Python version to help us optimize the Software for your environment.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- What We Do NOT Collect -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">What We Do NOT Collect</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            The Donjon Platform is designed with data privacy as a core principle. The Software does NOT intentionally collect or transmit:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-red-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Scan Targets</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- IP addresses, hostnames, URLs, or any identifier of systems you assess.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-red-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Scan Results and Findings</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Vulnerability data, compliance gaps, risk scores, or any assessment output.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-red-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Credentials</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Passwords, API keys, tokens, certificates, or any authentication material you configure in the Software.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-red-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Personally Identifiable Information (PII)</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Names, email addresses, physical addresses, or any other personal data of your employees or clients.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">
            In the event of unintentional collection of data described above, DonjonSec will promptly delete such data upon discovery or upon written notification by the customer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Telemetry by Edition -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Telemetry Controls by Edition</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            Telemetry controls vary by license tier. We are transparent about what each edition collects and the controls available to you.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b border-navy-700">
                  <th class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-400 font-medium">Edition</th>
                  <th class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-400 font-medium">Telemetry Status</th>
                  <th class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-400 font-medium">Can Disable?</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-slate-300">
                <tr class="border-b border-navy-800">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Community</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Enabled by default</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-navy-800">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Pro</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Enabled by default</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-cyan-400">Yes, via configuration</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-navy-800">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Enterprise</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Enabled by default</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-cyan-400">Yes, Zero Data Retention available</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">MSSP</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Customer-controlled</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-cyan-400">Yes, full control with audit rights</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- How We Use Your Data -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">How We Use Your Data</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            Data collected by the Software is used for the following purposes:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Product Improvement</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Understanding which features are used to prioritize development and improve performance, stability, and user experience.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Anonymized Statistics</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Aggregated, de-identified data may be used for internal reporting, market analysis, and public statistics that do not identify any individual customer.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">License Compliance</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Verifying that the Software is being used within the terms of the applicable license agreement.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Support and Troubleshooting</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> -- Diagnosing and resolving technical issues reported by customers, improving error handling, and delivering targeted fixes.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Data Retention -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Data Retention</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Telemetry data is retained for a maximum of twenty-four (24) months from the date of collection. License activation data is retained for the duration of the license term plus twelve (12) months. Customers may request deletion of their data by contacting
            <a href="mailto:legal@donjonsec.com" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">legal@donjonsec.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Data Security -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Data Security</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            All telemetry data is transmitted over encrypted channels (TLS 1.2+). Data at rest is stored using industry-standard encryption. Access to customer data is restricted to authorized DonjonSec personnel on a need-to-know basis.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Third-Party Sharing -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Third-Party Sharing</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            DonjonSec does not sell, rent, or share customer data with third parties, except as required by law or valid legal process. If we are compelled to disclose data, we will make reasonable efforts to notify the affected customer unless legally prohibited from doing so.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Changes to This Policy -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            DonjonSec may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be published at
            <a href="/legal/privacy/" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">donjonsec.com/legal/privacy</a>
            and, for material changes, communicated via email or in-app notification. Continued use of the Software after notification of changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            For questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact:
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-950 p-6">
            <p class="text-slate-300">
              <span class="font-medium text-white">DonjonSec -- Privacy Inquiries</span>
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-400">
              Email:
              <a href="mailto:legal@donjonsec.com" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">legal@donjonsec.com</a>
            </p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-slate-400">
              Subject line: <span class="font-mono text-cyan-400">[PRIVACY]</span> followed by your request
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
